title: Colleen's Slow Cooker Jambalaya
directions: In a slow cooker, mix the chicken, sausage, tomatoes with juice, onion, green bell pepper, celery, and broth. Season with oregano, parsley, Cajun seasoning, cayenne pepper, and thyme. Watch Now
Cover, and cook 7 to 8 hours on Low, or 3 to 4 hours on High. Stir in the shrimp during the last 30 minutes of cook time. Watch Now
ingredients: 1 pound skinless, boneless chicken breast halves - cut into 1 inch cubes
1 (28 ounce) can diced tomatoes with juice
1 pound frozen cooked shrimp without tails
